<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08161f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08161f">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08161f"> 161(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> religious clans</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The organization of early Irish monastic communities]</font> It was merely the clan or sept re-organized upon a religious footing. &ldquo;Les premi&egrave;res grands monast&egrave;res de l&apos;Irelande,&rdquo; says M. de Montalembert in his &ldquo;Moines d&apos;Occident,&rdquo; &ldquo;ne furent donc autre chose &hellip; que des <i>clans</i>, reorganis&eacute;s sous une forme religieuse.&rdquo; <small> Emily Lawless, <a name="ELIS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ELIS"><cite title="source">Ireland (Story of Nations series</cite></a> (192?) 40</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
